HEADWORD: Wineglassful
<hw>Wine"glass`ful</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>;, <plu>n. pl.
<plw>Wineglassfuls</plw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>.</plu> <def>As much as a
wineglass will hold; enough to fill a wineglass. It is usually reckoned
at two fluid ounces, or four tablespoonfuls.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Wineless</ent>⟦br⟧
